	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>April 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">You will please send<lb/> me a list of all subscribers for the Occident<lb/> in this city and the amt. of subscription due<lb/> from each&#44; as without that I shall never<lb/> succeed to collect enough to make a remittance<lb/> because some dispute the amt they owe<lb/> and others of their being subscribers<lb/> at all&#44; however I think I shall<lb/> be able to collect enough to make<lb/> a small remittance as soon as you<lb/> will send me the extract&#8212;</p>
				<p>As to <persName>Mr. Hirshfeld</persName>&#44; he told me some<lb/> time ago that he will send it himself<lb/> for the <add>Hebrew</add>.  You will do well to write<lb/> to him about it&#44; address in care<lb/> of <persName>Mssr Abrahams &#38; Co</persName> here.</p>
				<p>Your prospectus I have got&#44; but<lb/> no subscribers.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">in hope that you are well<lb/> and soon to receive that letter</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">A J Satz</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Rev&#58; Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
